o Open the terminal.
o Run the command
    su root
o Enter Password.
o Enter the command
    sudo visudo
o Note that there must be the line
    %sudo   ALL=(ALL:ALL) ALL
  after the line
    root    ALL=(ALL:ALL) ALL
o If the line
    %sudo   ALL=(ALL:ALL) ALL
  does not exist, add it after the line
    root    ALL=(ALL:ALL) ALL
o Press Ctrl+X to save the changes.
o Enter the following command
    sudo usermod -a -G sudo aamir
o It will add aamir to sudoers file.
o To cheeck if aamir is in sudoers file, enter the following command
    groups aamir
o The output of above command must show sudo along with cdrom and floppy etc.
o Reboot.
o You are done.
o Enjoy!
